''[[Rebel Dawn]]'' is the third book in ''[[Star Wars: The Han Solo Trilogy]]'' by [[A. C. Crispin]], and the final chapter in the [[Rise of the Empire era]].

The three volumes of ''[[Star Wars: The Han Solo Adventures]]'' cover a period of almost three [[Standard year/Legends|years]] during interludes in this novel.

==Publisher's summary==
''The ''Millennium Falcon'' is "the fastest hunk of junk in the galaxy." So when Han Solo wins it in a game of sabacc, he and Chewbacca become kings of the smugglers—uncatchable, unstoppable. But with the Empire clamping down, Han knows his luck can't last. Still, when an old flame of Han's, who is now the leader of an insurgent Rebel group, offers him a shot at an incredible fortune, Han can't resist. The plan seems a sure thing. The resistance will be light, the take enormous. Han and his friends will divide it equally with the Rebels. Too bad for Han that the planet of Ylesia is far from a pushover, that the Rebels have an agenda of their own, and that smuggler friends can often turn into enemies&hellip;faster than lightspeed.''

==Plot summary==
[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] wins the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] from [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] in an intense [[Sabacc/Legends|sabacc]] tournament on [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]]. He begins upgrading the [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] into a highly specialized smuggling vessel, and also makes a brief stop with [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] on the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] home planet of [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]], where Chewbacca marries [[Mallatobuck/Legends|Mallatobuck]]. Solo and Chewbacca then embark on a series of adventures.

After returning to [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]], Solo is reunited with his old flame [[Bria Tharen]], now an agent of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]. He is reluctant to aid his former love, who is planning an all-out attack against the slaving colonies on [[Ylesia/Legends|Ylesia]]. Promised appropriate compensation, Solo, Calrissian, and Chewbacca take on the mission. In the aftermath of the battle, Tharen's troopers turn their blasters on Calrissian and the rest of Solo's friends, confiscating all their valuables in the name of the Rebel Alliance. Angered, Han threatens to kill Tharen if he ever sees her again. Defaced and branded a traitor back on Nar Shaddaa, Lando refuses to believe Solo was not involved in the swindle, before proceeding to sock his former friend in the jaw.

Desperate for money, Solo and Chewbacca take on a [[Spice/Legends|spice]]-smuggling run from [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] (who had inherited his aunt's criminal empire) through the [[Kessel Run/Legends|Kessel Run]]. However, the duo are met mid-Run by an Imperial patrol, and forced to abandon their cargo in deep space, before The Falcon is searched and escorted to a nearby world. When they return in search for their cargo, however, the pair discover it has disappeared. The smuggler tries to explain to his employer what happened, but Jabba—in a drug-induced haze—turns his back on Solo, demanding compensation for the lost spice.

Meanwhile, Bria leads a rebel raid on [[Toprawa/Legends|Toprawa]] in which rebel spies transmit the plans for the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star I]] to [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] aboard the [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']]. Tharen and her squadron are all killed in the raid, but the plans are successfully transmitted. This is the "first victory" of the Rebels.

On [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], Han Solo tries unsuccessfully to arrange a personal meeting with Jabba, and becomes increasingly harassed by bounty hunters working for the crime lord. While he searches for a card game in which he might be able to win the money needed to pay off Jabba, he briefly encounters [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]].

Solo is then interrupted by news of his former lover's death, delivered by [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]], who also informs Solo that [[Greedo/Legends|Greedo]] is searching for him, and may try to kill him. The following day he records a message to Tharen's father, passing on the grim news.

The smuggler then proceeds to [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Chalmun's Cantina]] in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], where Chewbacca meets former Jedi Master [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], to discuss chartering the ''Falcon'' for passage to [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]]. Solo meets with Kenobi and young [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], leading to the events of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].

==Continuity==
''Rebel Dawn'' began with the fateful [[Sabacc/Legends|sabacc]] game that transferred ownership of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|Millennium Falcon]] from [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando]] to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]]. The book then incorporated deliberate gaps in the storytelling to allow for the [[Brian Daley]] [[The Han Solo Adventures (omnibus)|novels]] to occur, before picking up the narrative after those events. The book led directly into the events of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|A New Hope]], specifically Han meeting with [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] in the [[Mos Eisley/Legends| Mos Esley]] [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]].<ref name="TERC" />

